    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-01-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <head>No. 256.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Turner</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                        the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia,
                                        Liberia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">Jan</hi>. 24, 1872</date>.
                                (Received Feb. 27.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 34.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acquaint the
                            Department with the fact that Hon. J. J. Roberts was inaugurated
                            President of the republic of Liberia on the 1st day of January, 1872.
                            The term of office for the President is two years, and this is the fifth
                            time that his excellency President Roberts has been elected President of
                            Liberia. The occasion seemed one of general interest; quietude
                            prevailed; persons from all sections of the country were present. Having
                            been unable to procure a manuscript copy of the President’s inaugural
                            address, I am forced to forward by this mail printed copies thereof.</p>
                <p>I avail, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. MILTON TURNER.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
